The hearing of an appeal against the election of Governor Ndiritu Muriithi failed to kick off yesterday after one of the judges was bereaved. The case was before a three-judge bench comprising Fatuma Sichale, Asike Makhandia and Sankale ole Kantai in the Court of Appeal sitting in Nyeri. ALSO READ:

DP Ruto pledges health, water projects worth billions Only Ms Sichale showed up and informed the lawyers that Justice Makhandia had lost his father on Sunday. She said the appeal was filed on March 2 and, therefore, should be disposed by September 5. She directed that the case be heard on July 10 and 11. 